I did not post this explicitly to write a review, but to add to a trend I noticed.  I asked for my receipt back after paying with a card, and after I did this my server realized he had overcharged me, and did another charge. Ok, people make mistakes, no big deal.  But, I got the old receipt. He had added a shot of espresso to my drink. Well, not the drink.. just the charge. It seems like on that system, it'd be weird to accidentally do that. Ive never used Starbucks' POS, but is there an 'add espresso shot' button, or is it in a submenu? I wouldn't say anything, but the reviewers seem to indicate that this happens frequently.  If anyone notices an overcharge, leave a comment or something. It seems like a pattern. I'm not that mad, really thinking it is a mistake... or just sad that wages have stagnated in this country so bad that people need to supplement their paycheck 80c at a time. Or perhaps this person just wants to equal out an espresso shot he grabs in the morning, and a few google reviewers have noticed.  I'm going with it was a mistake, and giving full stars because everything else was perfect.
